      <h4 style="padding-left: 14pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 111%;text-align: justify;">» <span class="p">As per recent amendment(s) in the Income-Tax Rules (&quot;Rules&quot;) made vide the Income-tax (22nd Amendment) Rules, 2015, effective 1 January 2016. Rule 114B of the Rules as substituted, mentions transactions in relation to which Permanent Account Number (PAN) is to be quoted on all documents and includes sale or purchase of goods or services of any nature for an amount exceeding two lakh rupees per transaction (Sl. No 18 of the Table in Rule 114B).</span></h4>
      <p style="padding-top: 1pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p>
      <h4 style="padding-left: 14pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 111%;text-align: justify;">» <span class="p">Rule 114C (2) of the Rules as substituted reads as follows: &quot;Any person, being a person raising bills referred to at Sl. No 5 or 6 or 18 of rule 114B, who, in relation to a transaction specified in the said Sl. No., has issued any document shall ensure after verification that permanent account number has been correctly furnished and the same shall be mentioned in such document, or as the case may be, a declaration in Form 60 has been duly furnished with complete particulars&quot;. In case PAN is applied for and / or not available, Form 60 is to be duly filled and signed / verified and submitted with identity and address proof (KYC documents) as per the page 3 of form 60.</span></h4>
      <p style="padding-top: 1pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p>
      <h4 style="padding-left: 14pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: justify;">» <span class="p">You are therefore requested that your invoice / bill / payment acknowledgement / debit note / credit note, etc. should mention PAN of your entity as well as our PAN.</span></h4>
